               <head>Scroll of 10 transcripts and petitions to royal court and ministers, Kingdom of Avadh (Oudh)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115922 http://lccn.loc.gov/n85018147">
                  <summary>Scroll of 10 transcripts and original petitions addressed to an unnamed ruler, as well as officials and dignitaries of Avadh (Oudh/Oude), during the reign of Amjad ʿAlī Shāh; most petitioners are identified by signatures and adjacent dated seals; dates extend from 1229/1813 to 26 Jum. II 1259/24 July 1843; contains appeals for employment and government posts, reconsideration on dismissals from post, adjudication and mediation in disputes, housing and poverty relief, social interactions of prominent women, ministers, princes, and ethnic and religious groups (African women and Christian East India Company officials), mortgages, debt, fraud, theft, and misappropriation, as well as 2 instances of the presentation of dedicated literary works; IOL stamp 13 May 1909; creased with some damage; variations in dimensions of documents; various design schemes, some illuminated flamboyantly; set of 3 scrolls (IO Islamic 3783, 3784, 3785, possibly corresponding to lot numbers 9, 10, 11) acquired in the 'Hodgson' auction sale ([19]09-05-13)</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
               </msContents>
